bug.short_desc: Playground: Mix of native and qooxdoo scrollbars

long_desc.thetext:
When the editor or the log are resized native scrollbars are shown. The application part is using qooxdoo ones.
We should better harmonize this to achieve a better look.
Created attachment 416 Screenshot of the playground application (FF3/Linux)
Additional note: the native scrollbar of the editor is not fixable, because we are dealing with a iframe element. But we should take a look at the log part.
The easiest way to harmonize all scrollbars is to use native scrollbars in the whole application. Done in r21468.
